@logic-eval text
Use logic-eval for short deterministic rule sets written as explicit when/then blocks.
Prefer it when the step is a local check, scoring rule, gating rule, or simple branch decision that can be expressed declaratively and audited line by line.
The body must already be close to the supported rule syntax; logic-eval should never be used as a container for ordinary explanatory prose.
Avoid it for procedural transformations, free-form prose, or vague natural-language instructions that are not already close to the supported CNL.
